LaTeX Project Public License (LPPL), version 1.3c
====================================================

Preamble
--------

The LaTeX Project Public License (LPPL) is the license under which the
LaTeX base system and related files are distributed.

This license is designed to encourage maintenance, modification and
redistribution of LaTeX, while ensuring that those who maintain LaTeX
receive proper credit and that modified versions do not distribute
confusion among users.

Conditions of Distribution and Modification
-------------------------------------------

1. Activities other than distribution and/or modification of the Work are
   not covered by this license; they are outside its scope. In particular,
   the act of running the Work is not restricted.

2. You may distribute a complete, unmodified copy of the Work as you
   received it.

3. You may distribute a Derived Work provided that the following
   conditions are met:
   a) The Derived Work is distributed under the same LPPL license.
   b) The Derived Work does not imply that it is the original Work.
   c) The Derived Work is clearly identified as a modified version.

4. If you distribute a modified version of the Work, you must include a
   prominent notice detailing the changes.

5. You may use the Work to create and distribute Compiled Works, provided
   that any modifications to the Work are made available under the LPPL.

6. If you are the Current Maintainer of the Work, you may, if you wish,
   specify that a Derived Work may be distributed only after approval by
   you.

Full license text can be found at:
https://www.latex-project.org/lppl/lppl-1-3c.txt
